1
00:00:14,624 --> 00:00:16,500
Coming.

2
00:00:38,105 --> 00:00:41,408
Let me know when everything's dry.

3
00:00:41,408 --> 00:00:43,968
I finished cleaning the air conditioner
on the second floor.

4
00:00:43,968 --> 00:00:46,480
Thanks.

5
00:00:46,480 --> 00:00:49,250
Huh? Didn't you finish
doing the laundry just now?

6
00:00:49,250 --> 00:00:53,787
It might still be drying.
Running the dryer just once isn't enough.

7
00:00:53,787 --> 00:00:58,388
Won't it just fix itself again?
Shall we dry the laundry outside?

8
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:04,620
Drying the laundry really is such a pain.

9
00:01:04,620 --> 00:01:09,012
I hate it. And bringing in
the laundry is just as bad.

10
00:01:09,670 --> 00:01:11,580
How about folding it?

11
00:01:11,580 --> 00:01:14,772
I hate that just as much!

12
00:01:15,424 --> 00:01:16,948
Oh!

13
00:01:21,915 --> 00:01:24,084
Come on, Sho, hurry up.

14
00:01:24,084 --> 00:01:25,216
- Okay.
- All done?

15
00:01:25,216 --> 00:01:27,028
I overslept.

16
00:01:28,055 --> 00:01:29,923
There we go.

17
00:01:29,923 --> 00:01:31,692
- Azusa.
- Yes?

18
00:01:31,692 --> 00:01:34,128
Where's my T-shirt?

19
00:01:34,128 --> 00:01:36,096
Oh, maybe it's not dry yet.

20
00:01:36,096 --> 00:01:37,998
Sorry, Itsuki. Just make
whatever looks good for breakfast.

21
00:01:37,998 --> 00:01:41,869
- We're heading out now.
- Hey, hold on, hold on.

22
00:01:41,869 --> 00:01:44,672
High-fives and a hug.

23
00:01:44,672 --> 00:01:47,241
That's it.

24
00:01:47,241 --> 00:01:50,240
Let's go, Sho. Come on, hurry up.

25
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:52,256
Coming.

26
00:01:52,256 --> 00:01:53,536
All right, we're off.

27
00:01:53,536 --> 00:01:56,340
- We'll be back soon.
- Okay, see you later.

28
00:02:14,660 --> 00:02:15,536
[Marisia]

29
00:02:15,536 --> 00:02:18,784
[Episode 1]
This time, she's wearing a long train dress,

30
00:02:18,784 --> 00:02:22,609
so I feel like A is the more beautiful one.

31
00:02:22,609 --> 00:02:24,445
I agree.

32
00:02:24,445 --> 00:02:27,124
All right, so next let's consider
the colors and layout.

33
00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:30,420
What does everyone think?

34
00:02:30,420 --> 00:02:32,992
I'll be sending you the pamphlet
with the special feature on marriage rings.

35
00:02:32,992 --> 00:02:34,188
Can you check it over for me a little later?

36
00:02:34,188 --> 00:02:35,796
You got it.

37
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:42,388
Let's go grab some lunch, Sakiko.

38
00:02:45,696 --> 00:02:47,668
Did something good happen?

39
00:02:47,668 --> 00:02:49,980
I just got a boyfriend, that's all.

40
00:02:49,980 --> 00:02:51,905
What kind of person is he?

41
00:02:51,905 --> 00:02:55,092
Well, he's over a decade younger than me.

42
00:02:55,876 --> 00:02:59,179
Just as I'd expect.

43
00:02:59,179 --> 00:03:01,760
Perfectly aligned demand and supply,

44
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:05,344
plus the same views
and expectations of relationships.

45
00:03:05,344 --> 00:03:08,555
Ah, that's very important, isn't it?

46
00:03:08,555 --> 00:03:11,392
To feel relaxed together
and having a good time together.

47
00:03:11,392 --> 00:03:13,780
That's how you and Mitsuru are, right?

48
00:03:14,461 --> 00:03:16,263
Yes.

49
00:03:16,263 --> 00:03:21,902
But if you're with someone for a long time,
something will happen eventually, right?

50
00:03:21,902 --> 00:03:23,980
Dissatisfaction, or the feeling that
they're not like who they used to be.

51
00:03:23,980 --> 00:03:27,174
Not necessarily,
at least not with my relationship.

52
00:03:27,174 --> 00:03:29,620
Just that we don't have the same days off.

53
00:03:31,512 --> 00:03:36,083
That's great. I don't think I could stand it
if my husband was always at home.

54
00:03:36,083 --> 00:03:38,552
No, Mitsuru is really incredible.

55
00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:44,390
<i>He's been able to live together
with someone like me for all this time.</i>

56
00:03:47,161 --> 00:03:50,228
- Please bring this to the customer, Naoto.
- Got it.

57
00:03:51,999 --> 00:03:56,437
- Thank you for waiting. Your blended coffee.
- Hello.

58
00:03:56,437 --> 00:03:59,306
- Welcome.
- Welcome. Please take a seat.

59
00:03:59,306 --> 00:04:04,278
So what if we take this as the base,
and give it a crunchy texture on the outside?

60
00:04:04,278 --> 00:04:05,480
Right.

61
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:08,315
Oh, and maybe a little more of that sugar...

62
00:04:08,315 --> 00:04:11,284
- Thank you for your hard work.
- Please go ahead.

63
00:04:11,919 --> 00:04:14,040
- Mr. Sonoda.
- Yes?

64
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:15,422
Do you need these Financiers?

65
00:04:15,422 --> 00:04:17,758
No, feel free to take them.

66
00:04:17,758 --> 00:04:19,226
Doesn't your wife want any?

67
00:04:19,226 --> 00:04:22,262
No, she doesn't like Financiers.

68
00:04:22,262 --> 00:04:23,712
Really?

69
00:04:23,712 --> 00:04:27,092
- Thank you very much.
- Thank you.

70
00:04:37,811 --> 00:04:39,200
Huh?

71
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:40,704
Sorry.

72
00:04:40,704 --> 00:04:43,350
I'm having a hard time telling you
that standing and reading isn't allowed.

73
00:04:43,350 --> 00:04:45,018
Sorry.

74
00:04:45,018 --> 00:04:47,020
["Thirst for Love" By Yukio Mishima]

75
00:04:47,020 --> 00:04:49,089
Don't mix your personal items
with items that are for sale.

76
00:04:49,089 --> 00:04:50,591
It's really thrilling and enjoyable.

77
00:04:50,591 --> 00:04:53,161
If that book gets bought,
the bookmark goes too,

78
00:04:53,161 --> 00:04:55,162
so I put one of my favorites in there.

79
00:04:55,162 --> 00:04:58,644
Just what kind of thrill
are you getting out of this exactly?

80
00:05:02,903 --> 00:05:06,840
This box of cakes I got only has these in it.

81
00:05:06,840 --> 00:05:10,843
What's the difference
between Financiers and Madeleines?

82
00:05:14,081 --> 00:05:16,717
- Do you like them?
- Yes, I do.

83
00:05:16,717 --> 00:05:18,285
I'll have some.

84
00:05:18,285 --> 00:05:20,120
Thanks for the food.

85
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:22,623
- That was delicious.
- Thank you very much.

86
00:05:22,623 --> 00:05:24,358
Thank you very much.

87
00:05:24,358 --> 00:05:25,626
- Please come again.
- I will.

88
00:05:25,626 --> 00:05:27,860
Please come again.

89
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:31,892
- Shall we close up, Naoto?
- Okay.

90
00:05:46,380 --> 00:05:49,840
Sakiko likes these a lot,
so you made a huge batch of them on purpose.

91
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:51,885
Yes.

92
00:05:51,885 --> 00:05:53,880
So you admit it.

93
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:56,657
Well, it's because Sakiko earns more.

94
00:05:56,657 --> 00:05:59,426
I'd like to at least do this much for her.

95
00:05:59,426 --> 00:06:03,330
You usually call her that out in public too,
don't you, Mr. Seo?

96
00:06:03,330 --> 00:06:05,297
Yes.

97
00:06:05,899 --> 00:06:08,468
What else would I call her?

98
00:06:08,468 --> 00:06:12,239
Well, usually one would refer to the wife
as "my wife" or "my sweetheart".

99
00:06:12,239 --> 00:06:14,441
I see.

100
00:06:14,441 --> 00:06:16,116
Isn't it weird?

101
00:06:33,226 --> 00:06:35,508
- Thanks for doing the dishes.
- My pleasure.

102
00:06:40,801 --> 00:06:45,268
Is it really okay to be eating that
at this time of night?

103
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:49,480
I'll have it as a snack tomorrow.

104
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:52,948
I see. Tomorrow will be a busy day, right?

105
00:06:54,181 --> 00:06:56,149
The third Friday...

106
00:06:56,149 --> 00:06:58,418
Sorry. Did you not want to think about it?

107
00:06:58,418 --> 00:07:01,922
No, it's fine. I'll do my best.

108
00:07:01,922 --> 00:07:05,959
By the way, Mitsuru, how come
your shop is closed on Fridays?

109
00:07:05,959 --> 00:07:09,588
I'd like to change that,
but I do have regular customers.

110
00:07:10,197 --> 00:07:12,212
That's true.

111
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:15,335
Though as the shop manager,

112
00:07:15,335 --> 00:07:18,138
I do have the right to close the shop
and take time off whenever I want.

113
00:07:18,138 --> 00:07:19,732
I suppose that's also true.

114
00:07:20,741 --> 00:07:22,836
I want to take a trip somewhere!

115
00:07:24,344 --> 00:07:26,680
Okay.

116
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:28,281
Where do you want to go?

117
00:07:28,281 --> 00:07:31,220
Yuck! That tobacco smell stinks!

118
00:07:34,254 --> 00:07:37,290
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

119
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:41,664
All right, it's that time of the month again.
The third Friday, proofreading day.

120
00:07:41,664 --> 00:07:44,097
You probably didn't think
it would come this month, right?

121
00:07:44,097 --> 00:07:46,600
Well, believe or not, it's that time again!

122
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:48,035
Really?

123
00:07:48,035 --> 00:07:50,404
Let's do our best. Thanks in advance!

124
00:07:50,404 --> 00:07:54,500
[Wedding Items &amp; Bridal Accessories]
- Yes? - Could you check these materials?

125
00:07:57,477 --> 00:07:59,904
- I'm going now. Bye-bye!
- See you later.

126
00:07:59,904 --> 00:08:01,716
Please go ahead.

127
00:08:25,939 --> 00:08:29,428
- I'm home.
- Welcome back.

128
00:08:30,110 --> 00:08:33,684
- I made it through.
- Well done.

129
00:08:34,681 --> 00:08:36,750
There's food in the fridge.
Shall I warm it up?

130
00:08:36,750 --> 00:08:38,740
Okay. Thanks!

131
00:08:41,955 --> 00:08:44,628
- I'm home.
- Welcome back.

132
00:08:47,227 --> 00:08:48,495
You're back late.

133
00:08:48,495 --> 00:08:51,631
Yeah, things were pretty busy.

134
00:08:51,631 --> 00:08:54,000
- Hungry?
- Yeah.

135
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,828
Okay.

136
00:09:45,652 --> 00:09:48,621
Excuse me, are you
drying your laundry as well?

137
00:09:49,256 --> 00:09:51,291
Are you drying your laundry as well?

138
00:09:51,291 --> 00:09:53,627
Yes, just drying it.

139
00:09:53,627 --> 00:09:56,352
Okay, right over there.

140
00:09:56,352 --> 00:09:58,330
Thank you.

141
00:10:04,864 --> 00:10:11,911
[Money Exchange]

142
00:10:16,116 --> 00:10:18,018
Here, I have some small change.

143
00:10:18,018 --> 00:10:20,153
- It's okay. There's no need.
- It's fine, don't worry about it.

144
00:10:20,153 --> 00:10:21,288
About 20 minutes?

145
00:10:21,288 --> 00:10:24,457
- That's really not necessary.
- It's okay, it's only a small amount.

146
00:10:24,457 --> 00:10:28,052
- Even so, it's still money.
- It's fine, really.

147
00:10:31,064 --> 00:10:33,100
Then let me go buy you a cold drink.

148
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:34,880
- It's fine, you don't have to do that.
- It's so hot today.

149
00:10:34,880 --> 00:10:36,560
You really don't have to do that.

150
00:10:36,560 --> 00:10:38,580
But I want to drink something.

151
00:10:43,810 --> 00:10:46,413
- Thank you.
- It's nothing.

152
00:10:46,413 --> 00:10:48,982
It's fine, really.

153
00:10:48,982 --> 00:10:51,717
I bought two by mistake.

154
00:10:52,886 --> 00:10:54,644
Thank you.

155
00:11:03,296 --> 00:11:08,401
The dryer function on my washing machine
at home isn't working properly.

156
00:11:08,401 --> 00:11:12,639
And my husband told me that there's
a laundromat here, which is why I'm here.

157
00:11:12,639 --> 00:11:13,874
Ah, same here.

158
00:11:13,874 --> 00:11:15,542
Is your dryer also not working?

159
00:11:15,542 --> 00:11:19,079
No, no, we don't have a dryer at home.

160
00:11:19,079 --> 00:11:20,881
But drying the towels here
makes them soft and fluffy.

161
00:11:20,881 --> 00:11:26,353
- I see.
- So my wife told me to use the dryers here.

162
00:11:26,353 --> 00:11:30,323
I see... They become soft and fluffy.

163
00:11:30,323 --> 00:11:31,924
That's something to look forward to.

164
00:11:44,180 --> 00:11:46,380
Oh, you dropped something.

165
00:11:46,380 --> 00:11:48,814
Oh, sorry.

166
00:11:49,843 --> 00:11:52,720
Wow, this is so cute! It's tiny!

167
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:54,960
Ah, that's my son's. Sorry.

168
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:56,349
How old is he?

169
00:11:56,349 --> 00:11:58,551
He's five years old.

170
00:11:58,551 --> 00:12:03,189
Why are kids' clothes so cute?
They're just so tiny.

171
00:12:03,189 --> 00:12:06,191
This is what his socks look like.

172
00:12:08,695 --> 00:12:10,263
Do you live nearby?

173
00:12:10,263 --> 00:12:11,648
Yes, in an apartment building

174
00:12:11,648 --> 00:12:15,268
just across the bridge
along the river, facing the highway.

175
00:12:15,268 --> 00:12:18,292
- I also live near there.
- Oh, really?

176
00:12:19,906 --> 00:12:22,260
Ah, all done.

177
00:12:28,848 --> 00:12:30,983
So soft and fluffy.

178
00:12:31,918 --> 00:12:34,676
Hello. That's so cute!

179
00:12:36,690 --> 00:12:38,880
Do you have a dog or something at home?

180
00:12:38,880 --> 00:12:40,788
No, no pets.

181
00:12:44,898 --> 00:12:47,499
Thank you very much.

182
00:12:48,101 --> 00:12:50,452
[Seo]
This is where I live.

183
00:12:51,671 --> 00:12:53,556
All right, see you.

184
00:13:16,162 --> 00:13:18,100
I should probably fold the laundry.

185
00:13:48,028 --> 00:13:52,298
<i>I'm from the Traffic Division of Nanshin
Police Station, Nagano Prefectural Police.</i>

186
00:13:52,298 --> 00:13:56,368
<i>May I speak with a member
of Mr. Mitsuru Seo's family?</i>

187
00:13:57,470 --> 00:14:01,840
<i>I'm speaking with a family member
of Mrs. Azusa Sonoda, correct?</i>

188
00:14:02,609 --> 00:14:08,692
<i>Mr. Mitsuru Seo was on a bus that got into
an accident on a highway in Nagano Prefecture.</i>

189
00:14:12,218 --> 00:14:15,888
I'm on my way to the hospital right now.

190
00:14:17,323 --> 00:14:20,527
Look, I'm telling you, I don't know either.
Please, I'm begging you.

191
00:14:20,527 --> 00:14:25,931
<i>Ms. Azusa Sonoda is currently being
rushed to a hospital in Minami-Shinshu.</i>

192
00:14:46,786 --> 00:14:48,500
Dad!

193
00:14:52,358 --> 00:14:54,027
Itsuki.

194
00:14:54,027 --> 00:14:56,996
Sorry, Miki. You're heading
back to Nagoya, right?

195
00:14:56,996 --> 00:14:59,265
Sorry for making you come all this way.

196
00:14:59,265 --> 00:15:01,360
Hey, Sho. Was everything okay?

197
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:04,003
Were you a good boy?
What did you have for dinner?

198
00:15:04,003 --> 00:15:07,380
- I had five!
- Five? Five of what?

199
00:15:08,260 --> 00:15:09,976
Conveyor belt sushi.

200
00:15:09,976 --> 00:15:14,280
Oh? You had five plates of sushi?
That's a new record, isn't it?

201
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:16,583
- Itsuki.
- How much was the sushi?

202
00:15:16,583 --> 00:15:18,451
Oh, and the high-speed train.
You took the high-speed train, right?

203
00:15:18,451 --> 00:15:20,640
Or did you take a taxi?

204
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:23,957
No, no, this is your mom's.
You'll get scolded if you just take that.

205
00:15:23,957 --> 00:15:28,884
Where did I put it?
The money for the food and for the taxi.

206
00:15:30,363 --> 00:15:33,533
Your dad's still busy, Sho.

207
00:15:33,533 --> 00:15:35,168
What about Mom?

208
00:15:35,168 --> 00:15:38,037
Your mom's busy too.

209
00:15:38,037 --> 00:15:41,139
Would it be okay
if you stay with me until tomorrow?

210
00:15:42,275 --> 00:15:43,710
Okay.

211
00:15:43,710 --> 00:15:45,545
Thank you.

212
00:15:45,545 --> 00:15:47,168
Okay, say goodbye to your dad for now.

213
00:15:47,168 --> 00:15:48,884
Oh.

214
00:15:50,617 --> 00:15:54,319
High-fives and a hug.

215
00:15:58,258 --> 00:15:59,700
See you.

216
00:15:59,700 --> 00:16:01,667
Shall we go?

217
00:16:03,552 --> 00:16:05,865
Hold on.

218
00:16:05,865 --> 00:16:09,172
Tell Mom that I had five plates of sushi.

219
00:16:12,238 --> 00:16:14,139
Shall we go?

220
00:16:39,520 --> 00:16:41,420
Right this way.

221
00:16:59,136 --> 00:17:01,396
This belongs to my husband.

222
00:17:02,088 --> 00:17:05,740
No, maybe not.

223
00:17:05,740 --> 00:17:10,004
He's a nervous type, so I don't think
he'd let it get covered in scratches like that.

224
00:17:10,763 --> 00:17:12,631
What about this?

225
00:17:14,867 --> 00:17:18,196
Oh, I'm sorry! That's my husband's. Sorry.

226
00:17:21,474 --> 00:17:24,544
Can I take this home with me?

227
00:17:24,544 --> 00:17:26,379
Yes.

228
00:17:26,379 --> 00:17:30,415
We promise we'll conduct
a thorough search for its owner.

229
00:17:34,621 --> 00:17:37,620
Was anyone else rescued?

230
00:17:38,624 --> 00:17:40,308
No.

231
00:17:41,408 --> 00:17:43,092
Everyone?

232
00:17:43,712 --> 00:17:45,364
Yes.

233
00:18:02,592 --> 00:18:05,418
I wonder when he'll be found?

234
00:18:05,418 --> 00:18:08,820
Maybe tomorrow? Or the day after that?

235
00:18:09,956 --> 00:18:13,268
We'll conduct a thorough search.

236
00:18:19,632 --> 00:18:21,267
<i>This morning, just after 10 a.m.,</i>

237
00:18:21,267 --> 00:18:26,973
<i>a bus on a highway in Minami-Shinshu,
Nagano Prefecture, plunged off a bridge.</i>

238
00:18:26,973 --> 00:18:31,277
<i>At the time, there were 13 people on the bus.</i>

239
00:18:31,277 --> 00:18:37,450
<i>A total of 12 people died,
including the driver and 11 passengers.</i>

240
00:18:37,450 --> 00:18:42,255
<i>In addition, the whereabouts of
a man who was on the bus are unknown.</i>

241
00:18:42,255 --> 00:18:47,160
<i>A river runs underneath the bridge
from which the highway bus plunged.</i>

242
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:49,529
<i>It appears as if the man
was swept away by the river.</i>

243
00:18:49,529 --> 00:18:54,804
<i>The police and fire department are conducting
a search, but nothing has been found yet.</i>

244
00:19:21,194 --> 00:19:23,229
I think the laundry detergent
is sold separately.

245
00:19:23,229 --> 00:19:26,131
I see. Thank you.

246
00:19:30,136 --> 00:19:31,920
From the laundromat...

247
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:34,188
Yes, this morning.

248
00:19:37,310 --> 00:19:38,845
I didn't tell you my name.

249
00:19:38,845 --> 00:19:43,082
- Oh, I'm sorry. We didn't exchange names.
- Right. Sorry about that.

250
00:19:43,082 --> 00:19:45,120
But we met this morning, right?

251
00:19:45,120 --> 00:19:47,088
Yes, that's right.

252
00:19:47,787 --> 00:19:50,223
- My last name is Seo.
- Mine is Sonoda.

253
00:19:50,223 --> 00:19:52,624
What a surprise.

254
00:19:53,659 --> 00:19:57,760
If it's all right, I still have half left.

255
00:19:57,760 --> 00:19:59,232
Laundry detergent.

256
00:19:59,232 --> 00:20:01,768
Thank you very much.

257
00:20:01,768 --> 00:20:03,835
That's a big help.

258
00:20:10,243 --> 00:20:12,084
Are you traveling?

259
00:20:16,215 --> 00:20:18,388
My husband was in an accident.

260
00:20:20,787 --> 00:20:22,955
Did you see the news?

261
00:20:22,955 --> 00:20:26,259
A bus plunged off a bridge
not too far from here.

262
00:20:26,259 --> 00:20:29,194
And it appears my husband was on board.

263
00:20:30,630 --> 00:20:32,865
I was so surprised.

264
00:20:32,865 --> 00:20:35,601
He told me that he was just going out
for a bit, and that he'd be right back.

265
00:20:35,601 --> 00:20:37,652
Never expected it'd be in Nagano.

266
00:20:38,538 --> 00:20:40,940
I think I'm having trouble
drying the laundry again.

267
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:42,775
There's a laundromat, you know.

268
00:20:42,775 --> 00:20:45,378
It's just across the bridge.

269
00:20:45,378 --> 00:20:48,500
- Really? Maybe I'll go check it out.
- Sure.

270
00:20:49,215 --> 00:20:51,060
I'll be going out for just a bit.

271
00:20:51,060 --> 00:20:54,360
- You have the day off today, right?
- Yes.

272
00:20:54,360 --> 00:20:55,755
I'll be back tonight.

273
00:20:55,755 --> 00:20:57,560
Okay. Take care.

274
00:20:57,560 --> 00:21:00,529
I will. I'll be back soon.

275
00:21:04,797 --> 00:21:09,812
I broke out in this awful cold sweat,
so I figured I'd do some laundry.

276
00:21:17,343 --> 00:21:19,764
They haven't found my husband.

277
00:21:20,580 --> 00:21:24,308
But seriously, where could he be?

278
00:21:25,918 --> 00:21:28,372
Anyway, he might be probably fine.

279
00:21:29,889 --> 00:21:36,362
My husband was an inter-high school swimmer,
so maybe he'd be okay if he fell into a river.

280
00:21:42,535 --> 00:21:44,372
Me too.

281
00:21:45,104 --> 00:21:48,341
- You were an inter-high swimmer too?
- Oh, no.

282
00:21:48,341 --> 00:21:52,628
I meant, on the same bus. My wife.

283
00:21:56,315 --> 00:21:58,644
My wife has been found.

284
00:22:00,686 --> 00:22:02,708
She was dead.

285
00:22:08,528 --> 00:22:10,329
- <i>Azusa.</i>
- <i>Hmm?</i>

286
00:22:10,329 --> 00:22:13,165
- Look.
- Oh, the towels are fluffy, right?

287
00:22:13,165 --> 00:22:16,640
- Yes, I thought so.
- I dried them at the laundromat.

288
00:22:16,640 --> 00:22:19,539
You know, the place
just across the bridge, straight ahead.

289
00:22:19,539 --> 00:22:21,152
Oh, nice.

290
00:22:21,152 --> 00:22:24,210
All right, I'm going out for a bit.

291
00:22:24,210 --> 00:22:26,279
Huh? With whom?

292
00:22:26,279 --> 00:22:29,916
Hmm? Oh, a friend. No one you know.

293
00:22:29,916 --> 00:22:31,117
Take care of Sho.

294
00:22:31,117 --> 00:22:33,953
Oh, okay. Miki will be here soon anyway.

295
00:22:33,953 --> 00:22:35,740
All right, take care.

296
00:22:35,740 --> 00:22:37,524
I'm off.

297
00:22:42,662 --> 00:22:46,380
This is the postmortem examination report
that the doctor prepared.

298
00:22:46,380 --> 00:22:48,832
It's the same as a death certificate,

299
00:22:48,832 --> 00:22:52,212
so please take this to the government office
to complete the procedures.

300
00:22:54,112 --> 00:22:57,748
We'll contact you if anything else comes up.

301
00:22:59,879 --> 00:23:02,388
- Well...
- Yes?

302
00:23:04,850 --> 00:23:10,740
My wife... do you know who she was with?

303
00:23:42,488 --> 00:23:45,992
I told you that you didn't have to wear them.

304
00:23:45,992 --> 00:23:48,394
But you wore them anyway.

305
00:23:48,394 --> 00:23:52,664
The strawberry-patterned underwear
I gave you as a joke.

306
00:23:59,605 --> 00:24:02,674
I always use this.

307
00:24:03,576 --> 00:24:07,178
The thin bath towel.

308
00:24:11,784 --> 00:24:17,364
Mitsuru always uses the thick bath towel.

309
00:24:20,326 --> 00:24:22,196
Mitsuru's socks.

310
00:24:24,096 --> 00:24:26,036
Mitsuru's handkerchief.

311
00:24:31,203 --> 00:24:34,132
Mitsuru's T-shirt.

312
00:24:38,277 --> 00:24:40,180
It's huge.

313
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:31,029
[Closed]

314
00:25:36,268 --> 00:25:38,100
Sorry, not yet...

315
00:25:40,256 --> 00:25:42,452
Thank you for this.

316
00:25:51,150 --> 00:25:52,884
It's good.

317
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:57,790
Naoto, I'm so sorry about the shop.

318
00:25:57,790 --> 00:26:00,064
It must be tough doing this alone.

319
00:26:00,064 --> 00:26:02,528
You don't have to force yourself
to keep it open.

320
00:26:02,528 --> 00:26:04,820
He still hasn't been found, right?

321
00:26:05,440 --> 00:26:07,092
Not yet.

322
00:26:08,968 --> 00:26:13,844
Can I keep the shop open by myself
until Mr. Seo comes back?

323
00:26:16,408 --> 00:26:18,228
Thank you.

324
00:26:26,919 --> 00:26:29,260
I tried making this.

325
00:26:29,260 --> 00:26:31,423
Wow, I love these!

326
00:26:31,423 --> 00:26:33,620
Mitsuru often brings these home.

327
00:26:33,620 --> 00:26:35,820
They always don't sell.

328
00:26:35,820 --> 00:26:38,330
Oh? But they're good.

329
00:26:38,330 --> 00:26:40,276
Thank you for the food.

330
00:26:41,667 --> 00:26:43,540
Yum! This is good.

331
00:26:44,270 --> 00:26:46,068
Good.

332
00:26:54,368 --> 00:26:58,740
[Temporarily Closed]

333
00:27:35,554 --> 00:27:38,164
Things were just about to get interesting.

334
00:27:51,168 --> 00:27:52,838
Here are the documents.

335
00:27:52,838 --> 00:27:54,520
Thank you.

336
00:27:54,520 --> 00:27:58,356
[Accident Explanation]

337
00:27:59,612 --> 00:28:03,649
Actually, I just lost someone too...

338
00:28:03,649 --> 00:28:05,840
Mrs. Seo.

339
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:08,308
It couldn't be helped...

340
00:28:09,321 --> 00:28:11,323
The cause of the accident

341
00:28:11,323 --> 00:28:16,560
was due to the driver, a man in his 50s,
suffering a heart attack.

342
00:28:16,560 --> 00:28:19,164
This has been confirmed by the police.

343
00:28:19,164 --> 00:28:21,344
We conducted an internal investigation,

344
00:28:21,344 --> 00:28:25,104
and there were no issues with the driver's
work schedule or regular health checkups.

345
00:28:25,104 --> 00:28:27,904
Therefore, this matter

346
00:28:27,904 --> 00:28:31,677
- is uninsurable...
- So the bus company isn't responsible?

347
00:28:31,677 --> 00:28:34,313
Well, yes, so...

348
00:28:34,313 --> 00:28:38,016
- The work schedule...
- And the body of the missing person

349
00:28:38,016 --> 00:28:40,252
hasn't been found yet, right?

350
00:28:40,252 --> 00:28:42,656
Yes, search operations are still ongoing
downstream of the river,

351
00:28:42,656 --> 00:28:45,536
and the police riot squad
is investigating, but...

352
00:28:45,536 --> 00:28:47,760
Regarding the missing man,

353
00:28:47,760 --> 00:28:50,296
- we still don't know his whereabouts...
- That's why!

354
00:28:50,296 --> 00:28:53,265
This is absurd! Even in this situation,

355
00:28:53,265 --> 00:28:56,420
don't try to gloss over it
with the word "missing"!

356
00:28:56,420 --> 00:29:02,041
I'm telling you to take seriously
the fact that many people died!

357
00:29:02,041 --> 00:29:05,844
- That's right!
- Our families were killed!

358
00:29:05,844 --> 00:29:09,220
- Explain it to us!
- We...

359
00:29:09,882 --> 00:29:12,750
Please calm down.

360
00:29:13,852 --> 00:29:16,084
Give me back my daughter!

361
00:30:02,320 --> 00:30:04,020
Mitsuru!

362
00:30:05,471 --> 00:30:07,028
Mitsuru!

363
00:30:08,841 --> 00:30:12,177
- Mitsuru!
- Mrs. Seo!

364
00:30:12,177 --> 00:30:14,772
- Mitsuru!
- Mrs. Seo!

365
00:30:19,284 --> 00:30:21,780
Mi... Mitsuru!

366
00:30:25,157 --> 00:30:27,220
Mitsuru!

367
00:30:56,221 --> 00:30:58,180
Sorry about that.

368
00:30:58,180 --> 00:30:59,892
Oh, no need to apologize.

369
00:31:04,430 --> 00:31:06,264
Well...

370
00:31:08,167 --> 00:31:14,106
I think people in similar situations
can understand each other very well.

371
00:31:14,106 --> 00:31:16,212
And we live nearby.

372
00:31:18,610 --> 00:31:20,779
So...

373
00:31:20,779 --> 00:31:23,732
Well... why don't we help each other?

374
00:31:26,718 --> 00:31:29,044
Until your husband comes back.

375
00:31:44,369 --> 00:31:47,873
I was going to tell you to go home early.

376
00:31:47,873 --> 00:31:51,210
But if it's easier for you to work,
that's fine too.

377
00:31:51,210 --> 00:31:56,884
But listen to your body, eat, and sleep.

378
00:31:58,750 --> 00:32:01,252
You're way too good of a boss.

379
00:32:12,032 --> 00:32:15,732
[Itsuki Sonoda: Are you eating properly?]

380
00:32:25,264 --> 00:32:33,408
[I guess I'm managing somehow.
Is your child okay?]

381
00:32:36,221 --> 00:32:38,356
- Good evening.
- Good evening.

382
00:32:39,758 --> 00:32:41,026
Good evening.

383
00:32:41,026 --> 00:32:42,688
I'm Sho Sonoda.

384
00:32:42,688 --> 00:32:44,760
So cute.

385
00:32:44,760 --> 00:32:48,000
My name is Sakiko Seo.

386
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:51,488
Well... this one can be frozen.

387
00:32:51,488 --> 00:32:53,140
Oh, thank you very much.

388
00:32:53,140 --> 00:32:54,720
Does Sho have any allergies?

389
00:32:54,720 --> 00:32:56,708
- Oh, no, he doesn't.
- That's good.

390
00:32:56,708 --> 00:32:58,277
- Thank you very much.
- Okay, then.

391
00:32:58,277 --> 00:33:00,400
- See you.
- Excuse me.

392
00:33:00,400 --> 00:33:05,384
Hey, Sho. Mrs. Seo is leaving,
so say bye-bye.

393
00:33:05,384 --> 00:33:06,860
Let's play.

394
00:33:06,860 --> 00:33:08,224
Sho.

395
00:33:08,224 --> 00:33:09,280
All right.

396
00:33:09,280 --> 00:33:11,689
- Thank you.
- Oh, wait...

397
00:33:12,457 --> 00:33:15,559
- Sorry for the mess.
- No, it's fine.

398
00:33:22,340 --> 00:33:23,936
Well...

399
00:33:23,936 --> 00:33:27,138
About Sho... I understand.

400
00:33:27,873 --> 00:33:31,676
It'll be little by little
from now on, I suppose.

401
00:33:50,740 --> 00:33:54,532
Come on, Sho, let's go sleep on the bed.

402
00:34:07,112 --> 00:34:08,900
May I use the sink?

403
00:34:08,900 --> 00:34:10,649
Oh, you can just leave it.

404
00:34:10,649 --> 00:34:12,320
There's no more room...

405
00:34:12,320 --> 00:34:13,919
Sorry about that.

406
00:34:13,919 --> 00:34:15,000
I'll wash them.

407
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:18,100
- Oh, sorry.
- It's okay.

408
00:34:22,194 --> 00:34:27,020
Oh, and thank you for those side dishes.
That really helps a lot.

409
00:34:27,020 --> 00:34:28,567
I'm not very good at cooking.

410
00:34:28,567 --> 00:34:30,720
I'm the one who should be grateful.

411
00:34:30,720 --> 00:34:33,860
I made a lot of food in advance.

412
00:34:33,860 --> 00:34:36,020
Because Mitsuru eats a lot.

413
00:34:37,743 --> 00:34:41,146
Sorry. My husband...

414
00:34:41,146 --> 00:34:44,249
He looks like that,
but he's a big eater... oh, wait.

415
00:34:44,249 --> 00:34:46,132
You haven't met him, have you?

416
00:34:47,753 --> 00:34:50,940
- You both work, right?
- Yes.

417
00:34:50,940 --> 00:34:53,258
How do you split the housework?

418
00:34:53,258 --> 00:34:58,263
Oh, we didn't decide clearly.
It was like, 'whoever notices it does it'.

419
00:34:58,263 --> 00:35:00,299
It worked out well.

420
00:35:00,299 --> 00:35:02,601
I see.

421
00:35:02,601 --> 00:35:05,437
He's very kind and considerate.

422
00:35:05,437 --> 00:35:09,341
Well, that's just from my perspective.

423
00:35:09,341 --> 00:35:12,676
I guess maybe my husband
did more housework than I did.

424
00:35:13,412 --> 00:35:15,579
I see.

425
00:35:16,782 --> 00:35:18,516
Sorry.

426
00:35:22,354 --> 00:35:27,760
Living alone, the housework
is so easy. I'm so surprised.

427
00:35:28,694 --> 00:35:32,884
There's only one person's worth of dishes
to wash, and there's so little laundry.

428
00:35:34,933 --> 00:35:38,470
The air conditioner cools the room
so fast when you're alone.

429
00:35:38,470 --> 00:35:41,205
I even raised the set temperature
by one degree.

430
00:35:43,775 --> 00:35:45,940
- Mrs. Seo.
- Huh?

431
00:35:46,712 --> 00:35:51,380
Please stop thinking that
you living alone is better.

432
00:35:53,685 --> 00:35:56,084
Because he might still be alive.

433
00:35:57,222 --> 00:36:02,294
And because there are people who lost
their families, you think you shouldn't grieve.

434
00:36:02,294 --> 00:36:04,692
Please stop thinking that way.

435
00:36:07,532 --> 00:36:12,084
It's okay to show that you're struggling.

436
00:36:13,640 --> 00:36:19,476
Huh? It's hard to show it.

437
00:36:23,014 --> 00:36:27,780
It's not that I want to
see him or talk to him,

438
00:36:29,554 --> 00:36:33,123
but it's just that sometimes,
I just want him to be found quickly.

439
00:36:34,020 --> 00:36:36,020
Though of course, I hate it.

440
00:36:36,020 --> 00:36:40,308
The best thing would be
if he just casually came back unharmed.

441
00:36:42,334 --> 00:36:45,137
What kind of person is your husband?

442
00:36:45,137 --> 00:36:47,939
- Huh?
- Tell me what kind of person he is.

443
00:36:47,939 --> 00:36:51,510
When he comes back, I'll check the answers.

444
00:36:51,510 --> 00:36:54,324
- Check the answers?
- Yes. Like...

445
00:36:54,946 --> 00:36:59,540
Between the husband as seen by his wife,
and the husband as seen by others.

446
00:36:59,540 --> 00:37:02,304
I want to verify the consistency.

447
00:37:02,304 --> 00:37:05,323
Oh, I'm not too confident about that.

448
00:37:05,323 --> 00:37:09,027
Because I've already got
a 'loved one filter' on.

449
00:37:09,027 --> 00:37:11,200
- I haven't heard that in a while.
- Huh?

450
00:37:11,200 --> 00:37:14,332
We're not high school girls here.

451
00:37:14,332 --> 00:37:19,169
Even after getting married,
the filter is still on.

452
00:37:20,872 --> 00:37:23,604
Is he that wonderful?

453
00:37:24,910 --> 00:37:28,928
He said that he was born to marry me.

454
00:37:28,928 --> 00:37:31,750
Wow, that's so cheesy.

455
00:37:31,750 --> 00:37:33,885
He's a romantic.

456
00:37:33,885 --> 00:37:36,154
What did you say back when he said that?

457
00:37:36,154 --> 00:37:39,156
- Huh?
- What did you say back?

458
00:37:43,904 --> 00:37:46,798
Sorry to keep you waiting.

459
00:37:46,798 --> 00:37:49,333
Thank you.

460
00:37:54,973 --> 00:38:00,884
[Recommended Item: Daikon]

461
00:38:08,653 --> 00:38:12,958
<i>An express bus plunged off a bridge
in Minami-Shinshu, Nagano Prefecture,</i>

462
00:38:12,958 --> 00:38:16,561
<i>and since this accident that
left 12 dead and 1 missing,</i>

463
00:38:16,561 --> 00:38:18,797
<i>18 days have now passed.</i>

464
00:38:18,797 --> 00:38:23,034
<i>Today, bereaved families are still visiting
the site of the accident to protest.</i>

465
00:38:23,034 --> 00:38:29,241
<i>In this accident, one male passenger
in his 40s remains unaccounted for.</i>

466
00:38:29,241 --> 00:38:35,447
<i>Police believe he was swept away by the river
under the bridge, and continue their search,</i>

467
00:38:35,447 --> 00:38:38,383
<i>but he hasn't yet been found.</i>

468
00:38:38,383 --> 00:38:41,600
<i>Furthermore, according to
subsequent interviews with investigators,</i>

469
00:38:41,600 --> 00:38:47,668
<i>the bus driver lost consciousness
due to a heart attack prior to the accident.</i>

470
00:38:56,167 --> 00:38:58,132
It's still not dry.

471
00:39:05,060 --> 00:39:08,446
<i>Why? How many times are you going to do that?</i>

472
00:39:08,446 --> 00:39:11,182
<i>Yay! Can you see me?</i>

473
00:39:11,182 --> 00:39:13,718
<i>Look, look! Hey!</i>

474
00:39:13,718 --> 00:39:15,954
<i>Yay!</i>

475
00:39:15,954 --> 00:39:18,020
<i>Nagano...</i>

476
00:39:18,020 --> 00:39:19,600
<i>Over here.</i>

477
00:39:19,600 --> 00:39:21,893
<i>I'm definitely not giving you that!</i>

478
00:39:21,893 --> 00:39:23,795
<i>That's not true! Because...</i>

479
00:39:23,795 --> 00:39:27,231
<i>- Yay!</i>
<i>- I'm looking forward to it!</i>

480
00:39:27,999 --> 00:39:30,067
Mr. Sonoda.

481
00:39:32,771 --> 00:39:35,073
- Good evening.
- Hey.

482
00:39:35,073 --> 00:39:38,176
- Where's Sho?
- My sister came over.

483
00:39:38,176 --> 00:39:42,820
She said, "Why don't you go for a walk
to change your mood?"

484
00:39:42,820 --> 00:39:44,380
I see.

485
00:39:44,380 --> 00:39:47,252
I've gotten used to how easy
the dryer is here, so I came by.

486
00:39:48,553 --> 00:39:51,189
Hanging laundry is tough, isn't it?

487
00:39:51,189 --> 00:39:54,059
Is your dryer at home
still not working properly?

488
00:39:54,059 --> 00:39:58,320
That's right. It used to
just fix by itself before, though.

489
00:39:58,320 --> 00:40:00,732
By itself?

490
00:40:00,732 --> 00:40:05,170
When I complained to my husband
that the dryer was acting up again,

491
00:40:05,170 --> 00:40:09,940
usually by the next day,
it would be working again.

492
00:40:11,042 --> 00:40:12,978
Isn't that... you know?

493
00:40:12,978 --> 00:40:17,415
Maybe your husband
was cleaning the filter for you.

494
00:40:17,415 --> 00:40:20,251
I clean it too, you know.

495
00:40:20,251 --> 00:40:24,389
That lint trap that collects stuff.

496
00:40:24,389 --> 00:40:26,992
That place, right?

497
00:40:26,992 --> 00:40:30,612
That's the drain filter, isn't it?

498
00:40:31,930 --> 00:40:33,940
What about the drying filter?

499
00:40:35,066 --> 00:40:36,701
Huh?

500
00:40:36,701 --> 00:40:40,372
Isn't there a place like this?
Where dust collects.

501
00:40:40,372 --> 00:40:41,439
Huh?

502
00:40:41,439 --> 00:40:45,020
Whenever I go back to my parents' house,
they make me clean it.

503
00:40:45,020 --> 00:40:46,678
There's something like that?

504
00:40:46,678 --> 00:40:48,820
Maybe you've placed some things on top of it?

505
00:40:48,820 --> 00:40:52,244
I heard that if dust collects there,
the drying becomes less effective.

506
00:40:53,318 --> 00:40:55,253
Oh. Then...

507
00:40:55,253 --> 00:40:58,420
Maybe Mitsuru really was cleaning it for me.

508
00:40:59,760 --> 00:41:01,259
He's very kind.

509
00:41:01,259 --> 00:41:05,040
Yeah, though I wish he would have told me.

510
00:41:05,040 --> 00:41:07,399
That much I could do by myself.

511
00:41:07,399 --> 00:41:11,435
Maybe he wanted to see you happy,
saying "It's fixed!"?

512
00:41:14,906 --> 00:41:19,412
Your husband really is a wonderful person.

513
00:41:21,713 --> 00:41:23,348
Yes.

514
00:41:30,588 --> 00:41:33,716
But he was having an affair
with my wife, wasn't he?

515
00:41:35,694 --> 00:41:37,761
Huh?

516
00:41:39,431 --> 00:41:42,666
Oh dear, it's still not dry.

517
00:41:44,102 --> 00:41:47,638
Well... what is it?

518
00:41:54,813 --> 00:41:56,404
Well...

519
00:41:59,818 --> 00:42:04,948
Your husband was
having an affair with my wife.

520
00:42:09,461 --> 00:42:11,796
I was going to keep quiet a little longer.

521
00:42:11,796 --> 00:42:15,667
I wanted to find out more, but I'm sorry.

522
00:42:15,667 --> 00:42:17,716
I just couldn't take it anymore.

523
00:42:20,638 --> 00:42:23,207
It's the 'loved one filter,' right?

524
00:42:24,109 --> 00:42:26,132
You should clean it.

525
00:42:43,128 --> 00:42:44,576
- Hello.
- Hello.

526
00:42:44,576 --> 00:42:46,388
Excuse me.

527
00:43:40,652 --> 00:43:43,348
You usually call her that out
in public too, don't you?

528
00:43:43,980 --> 00:43:45,323
Hugs.

529
00:43:45,323 --> 00:43:47,100
Mitsuru!

